Difference between Local Storage and Session Storage? (6:47)

Local Storage: Data has no expiration time. It persists even if the browser/tab is closed until manually deleted (7:00).
Session Storage: Data is temporary and unique to a specific tab. It is cleared once the tab or window is closed (9:16).
How can page loading time be reduced? (10:11)

