What is the this keyword? (29:13)

Answer: It refers to the object that is currently executing the code. Its value depends on the "call site" (how the function is called) (29:30).
What is a CDN (Content Delivery Network)? (32:46)

Answer: A system of distributed servers that deliver web content based on the user's geographic location to reduce latency and speed up delivery (33:41).
Event Bubbling vs. Event Capturing? (34:01)

Bubbling: The event starts at the target element and moves up to the parents (34:40).
Capturing: The event starts at the top (window/document) and moves down to the target element (34:12).
What is "use strict"? (38:05)

